to build and run on arch linux
gradle build
gradle run
gradle bootRun

to build the cross platform version
gradle wrapper --gradle-version 2.13

option two
./gradlew build
./gradlew run
./gradlew bootRun


use bootRun to start the spring app insted of run

to build and run a jar:
gradle clean build &&  java -jar build/libs/grocery_search.jar

for DB will be using h2 as it is built in to Spring Boot supports H2, an in-memory relational database engine

